Frank Wennemer, Respondent v. Philip Braender, Appellant. Decided May 2, 1892. Appeal by defendant from judgment entered upon a verdict in .favor of plaintiff and from order denying a motion for a new trial. *461Bartlett, Wilson & Hayden, attorneys, and Philip L. Wilson of counsel, for appellant. Louis A. Wagner, attorney, and Lewis Sanders of counsel, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and McAdam, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
